- On the other hand, colleague, the tightening of sanctions is like a cold shower for our nomenclature, isn't it? - I completely agree with you, colleague, they will have to buy summer cottages in Sochi, invest in sanatoriums and health resorts, teach children at Moscow State University, be treated from us, to buy a Zhiguli and the Volga, where should they go when the Swift was turned off, the borders were closed, they will have everything like normal Russian citizens! Just look, our poor, unsociable economy will rise from its knees... It feels like we are going back to the USSR! - Most likely, to the analogue of North Korea.